---
import { goUrl, goAmazonUrl } from '@tagflow/core'
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <title>TagFlow × Astro static assets</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <main>
      <h1>Review: Flagship Remote</h1>
      <p>
        Build-time helper (<code>goUrl</code>) generates the redirect path, so
        templates never hand-write it — and adding marketplaces later never
        touches published content.
      </p>
      <p>
        <a href={goUrl('flagship-product')} rel="sponsored nofollow">
          View on Amazon
        </a>
      </p>
      <p>
        One-off link without a product entry:
        <a href={goAmazonUrl('B0XXXXXXXX')} rel="sponsored nofollow">
          View on Amazon
        </a>
      </p>
      <p><small>As an Amazon Associate we earn from qualifying purchases.</small></p>
    </main>
  </body>
</html>
